## Common Patterns

### Load or Create

```rust
pub async fn load_or_create_player(pool: &DbPool, name: &str) -> Result<Player> {
    match load_player_by_name(pool, name).await {
        Ok(player) => Ok(player),
        Err(_) => {
            let player = create_default_player(name);
            save_player(pool, &player).await?;
            Ok(player)
        }
    }
}
```

### Batch Inserts

```rust
// Good: Single transaction
let mut tx = pool.begin().await?;
for item in items {
    query!("INSERT INTO ...").execute(&mut *tx).await?;
}
tx.commit().await?;

// Bad: N transactions
for item in items {
    query!("INSERT INTO ...").execute(&pool).await?; // Slow!
}
```

## Logging

Log slow queries for optimization:

```rust
let start = Instant::now();
let result = query!("SELECT ...").fetch_all(&pool).await?;
let elapsed = start.elapsed();

if elapsed > Duration::from_millis(100) {
    tracing::warn!("slow query: {:?}", elapsed);
}
```

## Testing

Use `sqlx::test` for integration tests:

```rust
#[sqlx::test]
async fn test_load_player(pool: MySqlPool) -> sqlx::Result<()> {
    // Test DB is created/cleaned automatically
    let player = create_test_player(&pool).await?;
    let loaded = load_player(&pool, player.id).await?;
    assert_eq!(player.name, loaded.name);
    Ok(())
}
```
